Description:
Hi, we're experiencing some issues with our BGP routing. The AS Path is 65001 65002 65003, and the prefixes are 192.168.1.0/24 and 10.0.0.0/8. Here is the output from the 'show ip bgp' command:

BGP table version is 3, local router ID is 192.168.1.1
Status codes: s suppressed, d damped, h history, * valid, > best, i - internal
Origin codes: i - IGP, e - EGP, ? - incomplete

   Network          Next Hop            Metric LocPrf Weight Path
*> 192.168.1.0/24   0.0.0.0                  0         32768 i
*> 10.0.0.0/8       192.168.1.2              0         32768 65001 65002 65003 i

Can you check? Thanks, John Doe
